value.title: Chelsea Handler says 50 Cent 'wasn't serious' about supporting Trump
value.excerpt: Comedian Chelsea Handler details a phone call she had with rapper 50 Cent on "The View" after he expressed support for Pres. Trump and then renounced it.

value.title: Coronavirus Is A Key Campaign Issue: What's Joe Biden's Plan?
value.excerpt: With cases surging, the coronavirus pandemic is heating up as an election issue. Voters have seen President Trump's approach to the crisis play out in real-time, but how would Biden handle things?

value.title: Ari Fleischer: Biden is 'taking advantage of' a 'broken-down media' that is 'biased against Trump'
value.excerpt: The Biden campaign is "taking advantage" of the media bias against President Trump to keep the controversy surrounding former Vice President Joe Biden's son Hunter out of the spotlight, former White House Press Secretary Ari Fleischer claimed Wednesday.

value.title: Trump: Philadelphia police shooting a 'terrible event,' but rioting comes from group Joe Biden 'supports'
value.excerpt: President Trump called on Democrats in Philadelphia to crack down on recent rioting, and blamed Joe Biden for not condemning the unrest strongly enough.

value.title: Whitmer on Trump's response to kidnapping plot: "I don't think it's funny"
value.excerpt: Michigan Governor Gretchen Whitmer said his response to the plot against her "tells you everything you need to know about the character of this president."

value.title: Trump administration considers early biometric screening for visa seekers
value.excerpt: Some officials raise concerns about retaliation against American travelers

value.title: WATCH LIVE: Trump speaks at campaign rally in Bullhead City, Arizona
value.excerpt: Trump weighed in on two nights of clashes with Philadelphia police and store break-ins following the fatal shooting by police of Walter Wallace Jr.

value.title: Trump Administration Uses Philadelphia Protests To Illustrate ‘Liberal Democrats’ War Against The Police’
value.excerpt: The Trump administration said the protests in Philadelphia are “the most recent consequence of the Liberal Democrats’ war against the police.” The administration said all incidents of lethal force must be investigated,

value.title: Biden addresses violence in Philadelphia: 'No excuse' for looting
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden on Wednesday addressed the recent violence in Philadelphia over the police killing of Walter Wallace Jr., telling reporters that the death is not an excuse for looting or criminal activity.

value.title: Justice Clarence Thomas’ wife boosts unsupported claims against Joe Biden
value.excerpt: Other spouses of justices have their own professional lives, but Ginni Thomas is the only one whose work sometimes butts up against her husband’s.

value.title: Bill McGurn slams 'outrageous behavior' from media suppressing Hunter Biden allegations
value.excerpt: After Hunter Biden’s former business associate Tony Bobulinsky gave an interview on Fox News’ “Tucker Carlson Tonight” Tuesday, Wall Street Journal columnist Bill McGurn reacted to the interview pointing out that the story has been covered up by the media and social media companies.

value.title: Joe Biden could be compromised by Chinese Communist Party: Rep. Crenshaw
value.excerpt: Joe Biden needs to answer whether or not he's compromised by China before the Nov. 3 election, Rep. Dan Crenshaw, R-Texas, said Wednesday.

value.title: Hundreds attend rally to see Vice President Mike Pence in Greenville
value.excerpt: The vice president had landed in Greenville, an Upstate South Carolina city that is, in most regards, strongly considered to be Trump country. “I don’t want to lose this country to Joe Biden," said Dean Cox,

value.title: Hunter Biden engaged in ‘raw influence-peddling’ on grand, global scale: Turley
value.excerpt: Joe Biden and his family engaged in "legal corruption" despite claims of no wrongdoing, Fox News contributor Jonathan Turley argued Wednesday.

value.title: Ricky Martin says it's 'super sad' to see fellow Latinos back Donald Trump
value.excerpt: Ricky Martin discussed his support for Joe Biden and the “super sad” prospect of seeing fellow Latinos vote for Donald Trump.

value.title: Rehire Trump as national CEO to continue US economic renaissance: Steve Cortes
value.excerpt: President Trump will continue the thriving economy if re-elected, but Joe Biden threatens a reversal, Trump 2020 campaign senior adviser Steve Cortes told "Fox & Friends."

value.title: Election 6 days away: Biden back in Delaware as Trump heads to Arizona
value.excerpt: President Trump will hold two campaign rallies in the battleground state of Arizona on Wednesday as his Democratic rival Joe Biden, back in his home state of Delaware, hears a briefing from public health officials on the coronavirus pandemic with just six days left until the election.

value.title: Winnable but not yet won: Why Joe Biden and Mike Pence are both headed to Iowa this week
value.excerpt: The pair of visits, as well as Trump's rally earlier this month, indicate that both campaigns see the state as winnable but not yet won.

value.title: Trump uses outdated thinking in attempt to woo suburban women: I'm 'getting your husbands back to work'
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump offered his latest appeal to suburban women Tuesday evening, promising to get their husbands "back to work" if he's reelected.

value.title: Trump lifts tariffs on Canadian aluminum, warns he may resume them

value.title: Trump appears to give a pass to the domestic kidnapping plot against Whitmer
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump repeatedly attacked Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer, a Democrat, during his rally in Lansing, Michigan, on Tuesday, at one point taking credit for the FBI thwarting a plot to kidnap her and then immediately downplaying the actual threat that had been posed to Whitmer.

value.title: Trump Says Kamala Harris 'Won't Be First Woman President,' Rallygoers Demand Ivanka
value.excerpt: Trump said Kamala Harris will "take over" for Biden three weeks into his term if he wins before declaring, "she will not be the first woman president" Tuesday at a Lansing, Michigan campaign event.

value.title: Trump promised massive middle-class tax cuts in 2016. He delivered cuts, not as much on the middle class part
value.excerpt: The GOP tax bill in 2017 gave households an average $1,600 cut but the richest Americans, especially those making over $300,000, got the most relief.

value.title: Fact check: Trump falsely claims Pennsylvanians 'can't go to church'
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump keeps falsely declaring that various states run by Democratic governors are "closed" or "shut down."
